<header id="heading" data-0="background-position:center 0px" data-200="background-position:center -50px" data-500="background-position:center -200px">
    <div class="container" style="margin-left:50px">
      <h1>LifeTapper</h1>
      <h4>Discover your Life. <span style="color:lightgreen">One tap at time.</span></h4>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div id="skrollr-body">

    <div id="white-section-container" class="text-center">
      <div class="row-fluid">
        <h1 style="color:grey">What is LifeTapper?</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="row-fluid" style="padding-top: 50px">
        <div class="span4 offset1">
          <img src="assets/nexus-5.jpg" style="border-radius:10px"/>
        </div>
        <div class="span6 text-center" style="padding-top: 100px">
          <p>
            Lifetapper helps users keep track of any thing they would like to keep track of.
          </p>

          <p>
            With the help of smartphones, users may record data on the fly or at any time it is convenient.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="life-section-container" class="text-center" style="margin-top:15px"
    data-800="background-position:center 0px"
    data-800="background-position:center -25px"
    data-900="background-position:center -50px"
    data-1000="background-position:center -75px"
    data-1100="background-position:center -100px"
    data-1200="background-position:center -125px"
    data-1300="background-position:center -150px"
    data-1400="background-position:center -175px"
    data-1500="background-position:center -200px">
    <div style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.5); padding-top: 50px; padding-bottom: 50px">
      <div class="row-fluid">
        <h1>How does it work?</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="row-fluid" style="padding-top: 50px">
        <div class="span12 text-center" style="padding-top: 30px; padding-left: 25px; padding-right: 25px">
          <p>
            Lifetapper helps you create and log activities.
            Users may use our Web or Android applcation to log and view the times that engaged in these activites.
          </p>

          <p>
            Our Web application offers simple intuitive design to make it hassel free for users to log their data.
            Our Android application makes it even easier by enabling Near Field Communication to users to log events.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="white-section-container" class="text-center">
    <div class="row-fluid" >
      <h1 style="color:grey">Near Field Comunication</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="row-fluid" style="padding-top: 50px">
      <div class="span4 offset1">
        <img src="assets/nfc_stickers.jpg" style="border-radius:10px"/>
      </div>
      <div class="span6 text-center" style="padding-top: 30px">
        <p>
          LifeTapper allows users to use their NFC enabled phones as a remote for their
          accounts.
        </p>
        <p>
          By tapping your phones on NFC stickers, you may associate that sticker
          with an Event. Tapping associated stickers let users simply add dates or start / end
          a session for an Event.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="join-section-container" class="text-center" style="margin-top:15px">
    <div style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.5); padding-top: 50px; padding-bottom: 50px">
      <div class="row-fluid">
        <h1>Counts and Sessions</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="row-fluid" style="padding-top: 50px">
        <div class="span12 text-center" style="padding-top: 30px; padding-left: 25px; padding-right: 25px">
          <p>
            We allow two types of activites for users. Counts and Sessions.
          </p>

          <p>
            A Count is just a date stamp of the time the user completed an activity. For example, this could be the amount of times you have brushed your teeth.
          </p>

          <p>
            A Session lets users log the start and end times of an event. For example, it could be the time it took to complete an assignment of task.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="white-section-container" class="text-center">
    <div class="row-fluid" >
      <h1 style="color:grey">Join Now</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="row-fluid" style="padding-top: 50px">
      <div class="span12 text-center" style="padding-top: 30px">
        <p>
          Joining is simple, just click on the "Sign Up" button on the top right of the page and start getting active!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>
